      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a strong take. But what about the cost to regular people? I've heard that if we put tariffs on things like steel or electronics, the prices just go up for everyone buying stuff at the store. Isn't that basically just a tax on the average consumer?",
