    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait \"small price to pay\"? that seems kinda dismissive of people struggling with inflation. also, what about the industries that actually use those materials? like if steel gets expensive, car manufacturers and construction companies might have to lay people off because their costs are too high. isn't it true that tariffs can actually destroy jobs in other sectors even if they save some in others?",
